The paper discusses anonymization techniques for network logs and evaluates their impact on the utility of the logs for intrusion detection. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of designing and implementing the anonymization policies. Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of databases (cs.DB) as it deals with the management and analysis of large amounts of log data.
